                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1309">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.77/132.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 13, 1912</hi>
                        </date>,</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>By direction of the President the border consulates were to-day instructed as
                    follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Telegraph Department how many American railway conductors and locomotive
                            engineers who were formerly employed in Mexico are now idle in Texas
                            border towns opposite your post.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Whatever information you may have on the subject you will send to the
                    Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
